const ARTICLE_CONTENT={
  'deploy-custom-domain':{
    title:'Setting Up a Custom Domain',
    topic:'deploy',topicName:'DEPLOYMENT & ONBOARDING',
    type:'GUIDE',typeColor:'var(--deploy2)',
    read:'7 min',updated:'Mar 21, 2026',author:'Lightek Deploy Team',
    sections:['Overview','DNS Configuration','SSL Certificate','Verification','Troubleshooting'],
    body:`
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Every Lightek deployment ships with a default subdomain at <em>your-org.lightek.app</em>. For white-label deployments, you'll want to point your own domain — something like <em>platform.yourorganization.com</em> — at your instance. This guide covers the complete setup from DNS to live SSL.</p>
      <div class="art-callout info"><div class="ac-icon">ℹ️</div><div class="ac-body"><div class="acb-label">DISTRIBUTOR TIER REQUIRED</div><div class="acb-text">Custom domain setup requires Distributor or Master Partner tier. Associate resellers use the default <em>.lightek.app</em> subdomain. <a onclick="showArticle('res-tiers')">Upgrade your tier →</a></div></div></div>

      <h2>DNS Configuration</h2>
      <p>You need to add a CNAME record to your domain's DNS settings. This points your custom domain at your Lightek deployment endpoint.</p>
      <div class="art-steps">
        <div class="art-step"><div class="as-num">1</div><div class="as-body"><div class="asb-title">Log into your domain registrar</div><div class="asb-desc">Go to your domain registrar (GoDaddy, Namecheap, Cloudflare, etc.) and navigate to the DNS management panel for your domain.</div></div></div>
        <div class="art-step"><div class="as-num">2</div><div class="as-body"><div class="asb-title">Add a CNAME record</div><div class="asb-desc">Create a new CNAME record. Set the <strong>Name/Host</strong> to the subdomain you want to use (e.g. <em>platform</em> for platform.yourorg.com). Set the <strong>Value/Target</strong> to your Lightek deployment endpoint, found in your Reseller Portal under Instance Settings.</div></div></div>
        <div class="art-step"><div class="as-num">3</div><div class="as-body"><div class="asb-title">Set TTL to 300 seconds</div><div class="asb-desc">A lower TTL speeds up propagation. Set it to 300 (5 minutes) for now. You can increase it to 3600 after the domain is verified.</div></div></div>
        <div class="art-step"><div class="as-num">4</div><div class="as-body"><div class="asb-title">Enter your domain in the Reseller Portal</div><div class="asb-desc">Navigate to your instance in the Reseller Portal → Instance Settings → Custom Domain. Enter your full domain (e.g. platform.yourorganization.com) and click Save.</div></div></div>
        <div class="art-step"><div class="as-num">5</div><div class="as-body"><div class="asb-title">Wait for propagation</div><div class="asb-desc">DNS propagation typically takes 5–30 minutes, though it can take up to 24 hours. Lightek will automatically detect when your DNS is pointing correctly.</div></div></div>
      </div>

      <h2>SSL Certificate</h2>
      <p>Lightek automatically provisions and renews SSL certificates via Let's Encrypt once your DNS is verified. You don't need to upload a certificate manually unless you have a specific requirement for an extended validation (EV) certificate.</p>
      <div class="art-callout tip"><div class="ac-icon">✅</div><div class="ac-body"><div class="acb-label">AUTOMATIC RENEWAL</div><div class="acb-text">Lightek renews your SSL certificate automatically 30 days before expiration. You don't need to do anything. If renewal fails, you'll receive an email and a support ticket will be auto-created.</div></div></div>
      <p>If you need to upload a custom SSL certificate (for EV certificates or corporate PKI requirements):</p>

      <div class="art-code"><span class="code-lang">PEM FORMAT</span><button class="code-copy" onclick="this.textContent='✓ COPIED'">COPY</button><pre><span class="cm"># Your certificate chain should be in this order:</span>
<span class="cm"># 1. Your domain certificate</span>
<span class="cm"># 2. Intermediate certificate(s)</span>
<span class="cm"># 3. Root certificate (optional)</span>

-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
<span class="str">MIIFazCCA1OgAwIBAgIRAIIQz7DSQONZRGPgu2OCiwAwDQYJKoZIhvcNAQEL</span>
<span class="str">... your certificate data ...</span>
-----END CERTIFICATE-----</pre></div>

      <h2>Verification</h2>
      <p>After DNS propagates and SSL provisions, verify your setup by visiting your custom domain in a browser. You should see:</p>
      <table class="art-table">
        <tr><th>CHECK</th><th>WHAT TO LOOK FOR</th><th>STATUS</th></tr>
        <tr><td>HTTPS lock icon</td><td>Browser shows a padlock in the address bar</td><td>SSL active</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Domain resolves</td><td>Your deployment loads at the custom domain</td><td>DNS correct</td></tr>
        <tr><td>No certificate warning</td><td>Browser doesn't show a security warning</td><td>Cert valid</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Portal status</td><td>Reseller Portal shows domain as "VERIFIED"</td><td>Lightek confirmed</td></tr>
      </table>

      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <div class="art-callout warn"><div class="ac-icon">⚠️</div><div class="ac-body"><div class="acb-label">COMMON MISTAKE</div><div class="acb-text">The most common setup error is adding an A record instead of a CNAME. Lightek deployments use dynamic IPs — always use CNAME, never A record.</div></div></div>
      <p><strong>Domain not resolving after 30 minutes:</strong> Use a DNS propagation checker (e.g. dnschecker.org) to verify your CNAME is live globally. If it's not showing, double-check the record name and value in your registrar.</p>
      <p><strong>SSL certificate not provisioning:</strong> Ensure your CNAME is pointing to your exact Lightek endpoint (copy-paste from the Portal — don't type it manually). SSL cannot provision until DNS is verified.</p>
      <p><strong>Certificate warning in browser:</strong> Clear your browser cache, then try an incognito window. If the warning persists, the certificate hasn't finished provisioning — wait 10 minutes and try again.</p>
    `,
    related:['tr-custom-domain','deploy-ssl','deploy-go-live','start-whitelabel'],
  },
