      <div class="art-callout info"><div class="ac-icon">ℹ️</div><div class="ac-body"><div class="acb-label">CONSTITUTIONAL REQUIREMENT</div><div class="acb-text">The Ministry Engine is mandated by DYMOND Empire's Constitutional framework. All Lightek resellers agreed to its operation as part of the Lightek Reseller Agreement. Citizens on your platform are protected by it regardless of your configuration choices.</div></div></div>
      <p>The Ministry Engine operates across seven protocols. Each protocol governs a specific dimension of citizen interaction, content rights, or community ethics. All seven are active on every deployment by default.</p>

      <h2>The Seven Protocols</h2>
      <h3>1. Grace-First Matching</h3>
      <p>Applies to: <em>MATCH module, COMMUNITY module</em>. Ensures all citizen matching — whether for relationships, community groups, or service connections — prioritizes compatibility factors over algorithmic engagement optimization. Prohibits dark patterns designed to maximize time-on-platform at the expense of citizen wellbeing.</p>

      <h3>2. Prayer Recovery Protocol</h3>
      <p>Applies to: <em>WELLNESS module, CHURCH module</em>. Activates pastoral counseling pathways when citizen behavior patterns indicate distress. Does not diagnose. Routes to human counselors and prayer resources. Citizen data used by this protocol is never stored in analytics systems.</p>

      <h3>3. Cultural Sovereignty Filter</h3>
      <p>Applies to: <em>SOCIAL module, STUDIO module, BARS module</em>. Enforces Article V (Cultural Sovereignty) and Article VI (Cultural Attribution). Prevents algorithmic suppression of cultural content. Ensures attribution tracking is active on all content published through the platform.</p>

      <h3>4. Ownership Protection Layer</h3>
      <p>Applies to: <em>CLOUD module, STUDIO module, BANK module</em>. Implements Article I (Freedom of Ownership). Prevents the platform operator from claiming ownership of citizen-created content. Maintains immutable ownership records for all content uploaded through the STUDIO module.</p>

      <h3>5. Economic Equity Override</h3>
      <p>Applies to: <em>BANK module, REAL ESTATE module</em>. Implements Article II (Economic Participation) and Article VIII (Universal Access). Maintains the zero-interest, zero-collateral lending floor for qualifying citizens. Cannot be configured to exclude citizens based on protected characteristics.</p>

      <h3>6. Body As Temple — FIT Protocol</h3>
      <p>Applies to: <em>FIT module, WELLNESS module, CHURCH module</em>. Prevents the platform from promoting extreme dietary restriction, disordered exercise behaviors, or supplement products without appropriate qualification review. Integrates pastoral wellness framing into fitness content where applicable.</p>

      <h3>7. Restorative Justice Path</h3>
      <p>Applies to: <em>JUSTICE module, SETS module, COMMUNITY module</em>. Routes conflict resolution requests through restorative frameworks before punitive action. Requires a documented mediation attempt before citizen suspension or removal can be executed.</p>

      <h2>Module Coverage Matrix</h2>
