    sections:['Overview','API Keys','Bearer Token Flow','Scopes','Key Rotation'],
    body:`
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>The Lightek API uses API key authentication for server-to-server requests. All API calls must include an <em>Authorization</em> header with a valid Bearer token. API keys are scoped to specific modules and operations — a key provisioned for the BANK module cannot access STREAMING endpoints.</p>

      <div class="art-callout warn"><div class="ac-icon">⚠️</div><div class="ac-body"><div class="acb-label">KEEP KEYS SECRET</div><div class="acb-text">Never expose API keys in client-side code, public repositories, or log files. Treat them like passwords. If a key is compromised, rotate it immediately from your Reseller Portal.</div></div></div>

      <h2>API Keys</h2>
      <p>Generate API keys from your Reseller Portal: <em>Instance Settings → API Access → Generate Key</em>. You'll see the full key once — copy it immediately. After creation, only the last four characters are visible.</p>

      <div class="art-code"><span class="code-lang">SHELL</span><button class="code-copy" onclick="this.textContent='✓ COPIED'">COPY</button><pre><span class="cm"># Test your API key</span>
<span class="kw">curl</span> -X GET https://api.lightek.io/v1/auth/verify \
  -H <span class="str">"Authorization: Bearer lkt_live_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"</span> \
  -H <span class="str">"Content-Type: application/json"</span></pre></div>

      <h2>Bearer Token Flow</h2>
      <p>For requests on behalf of specific citizens, exchange your API key for a short-lived Bearer token tied to that citizen's session:</p>

      <div class="art-code"><span class="code-lang">JAVASCRIPT</span><button class="code-copy" onclick="this.textContent='✓ COPIED'">COPY</button><pre><span class="kw">const</span> response = <span class="kw">await</span> fetch(<span class="str">'https://api.lightek.io/v1/auth/token'</span>, {
  method: <span class="str">'POST'</span>,
  headers: {
    <span class="key">'Authorization'</span>: <span class="str">\`Bearer \${API_KEY}\`</span>,
    <span class="key">'Content-Type'</span>: <span class="str">'application/json'</span>,
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    <span class="key">citizen_id</span>: <span class="str">'cit_abc123'</span>,
    <span class="key">scope</span>: [<span class="str">'bank:read'</span>, <span class="str">'bank:write'</span>],
    <span class="key">expires_in</span>: <span class="num">3600</span>, <span class="cm">// seconds</span>
  })
});

<span class="kw">const</span> { token, expires_at } = <span class="kw">await</span> response.json();
<span class="cm">// Use token in subsequent requests on behalf of this citizen</span></pre></div>

      <h2>Scopes</h2>
      <table class="art-table">
        <tr><th>SCOPE</th><th>MODULE</th><th>DESCRIPTION</th></tr>
        <tr><td><code style="font-family:var(--fm);font-size:10px;color:var(--cyan2);">bank:read</code></td><td>BANK</td><td>Read account balances, transaction history, loan status</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code style="font-family:var(--fm);font-size:10px;color:var(--cyan2);">bank:write</code></td><td>BANK</td><td>Initiate transfers, create accounts, update profile</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code style="font-family:var(--fm);font-size:10px;color:var(--cyan2);">stream:read</code></td><td>STREAMING</td><td>Read content library, viewer sessions</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code style="font-family:var(--fm);font-size:10px;color:var(--cyan2);">stream:publish</code></td><td>STREAMING</td><td>Upload content, initiate live streams</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code style="font-family:var(--fm);font-size:10px;color:var(--cyan2);">citizen:read</code></td><td>ALL</td><td>Read citizen profile and preferences</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code style="font-family:var(--fm);font-size:10px;color:var(--cyan2);">citizen:write</code></td><td>ALL</td><td>Update citizen profile, preferences, settings</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code style="font-family:var(--fm);font-size:10px;color:var(--cyan2);">admin:*</code></td><td>ALL</td><td>Full administrative access. Handle with care.</td></tr>
      </table>

      <h2>Key Rotation</h2>
      <p>Rotate your API keys periodically and immediately if you suspect compromise. Rotation does not cause downtime — the old key remains valid for 15 minutes after the new key is generated, giving you time to deploy the update.</p>
      <div class="art-steps">
        <div class="art-step"><div class="as-num">1</div><div class="as-body"><div class="asb-title">Generate a new key</div><div class="asb-desc">In your Reseller Portal: Instance Settings → API Access → Rotate Key. Your new key is displayed once.</div></div></div>
        <div class="art-step"><div class="as-num">2</div><div class="as-body"><div class="asb-title">Deploy the new key</div><div class="asb-desc">Update your application's environment variables or secrets manager with the new key value.</div></div></div>
        <div class="art-step"><div class="as-num">3</div><div class="as-body"><div class="asb-title">Verify before the grace period ends</div><div class="asb-desc">Confirm your application is successfully authenticating with the new key before the 15-minute grace period expires for the old key.</div></div></div>
      </div>
    `,
